rface of [[Mars]] using its thermal emission imaging system.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wired.com/2009/02/feb-19-2002-odyssey-turns-its-cameras-on-mars/|title=Odyssey Turns Its Cameras on Mars|last=Long|first=Tony|date=2002-01-19|work=|newspaper=Wired|language=en-US|access-date=2017-01-27|via=}}</ref>\n* [[February 22]] \u2013 [[UNITA]] guerilla leader [[Jonas Savimbi]] is killed in clashes against government troops led by [[President of Angola|Angolan President]] [[Jos\u00e9 Eduardo dos Santos]] in [[Moxico Province]], [[Angola]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/1839252.stm|title=Savimbi 'died with gun in hand'|last=|first=|date=2002-02-25|work=|newspaper=BBC News|access-date=2016-06-04|via=}}</ref> His death leads to the end of the [[Angolan Civil War]] on April 4.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/africaandindianocean/angola/1389946/Unita-signs-peace-treaty-with-Angolan-army-to-end-27-year-civil-war.html|title=Unita signs peace treaty with Angolan army to end 27-year civil war|last=Butcher|first=Tim|date=2002-04-05|work=|newspaper=The Telegraph|language=en|access-date=2017-01-27|via=}}</ref>\n\n===March===\n* [[March 1]] \u2013 The [[Envisat]] [[environmental satellite]] is launched, with its purpose being the recording of information on environmental change.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/science/2002/mar/01/spaceexploration.environment|title=New satellite will monitor global warming|last=|first=|date=2002-03-01|work=|last2=|newspaper=The Guardian|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|access-date=2017-01-27|via=}}</ref>\n* [[March 27]] \u2013 A Palestinian [[Passover massacre|suicide bomber kills]] 30 people and injures 140 others at a hotel in [[Netanya]], [[Israel]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.timesofisrael.com/ten-years-after-passover-bombing-survivors-return-to-netanyas-park-hotel/|title=Ten years after Passover blast, survivors return to Park Hotel|last=Friedman|first=Matti|date=2012-03-27