egassun.com/news/1998/jun/20/memories-linger-for-victims-mother/ |title=Memories linger for victim\u2019s mother |publisher=Lasvegassun.com |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| September 21, 1990\n| [[Houston, Texas]], United States\n| ..., 16\n| 1 dead\n|\n| A 16-year-old girl fatally stabbed her classmate, 18-year-old Anthony Johnson, in the upper back with a [[hunting knife]] in a classroom at [[Jesse H. Jones High School]], in [[Houston]], [[Texas]]; Johnson later died at [[Ben Taub Hospital]]. The suspect was then placed in the Harris County Juvenile Probation Department. It was reported that the possible motive was the victim making an insulting comment about the suspect's clothing.<ref>Markley, Melanie. \"[http://www.chron.com/CDA/archives/archive.mpl?id=1996_1371129 Studying our Schools: Challenges / Safety matters: Issue is No. 1 concern with parents].\" ''[[Houston Chronicle]]''. October 13, 1996.</ref><ref>Hanson, Eric. \"[http://www.chron.com/CDA/archives/archive.mpl?id=1990_731137 Teen fatally stabbed in classroom / Victim pays for insult to girl's shorts with life].\" ''[[Houston Chronicle]]''. September 22, 1990.</ref>\n|-\n| April 10, 1991\n| [[Glasgow]], [[Scotland]], United Kingdom\n| Barbara Glover, 16\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 16-year-old Diane Watson is stabbed to death by 16-year-old Barbara Glover at Whitehill Secondary School in the Dennistoun area of Glasgow.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/scotland/616759.stm|work=BBC News|title=Parents protest at killer's parole bid|date=January 24, 2000|accessdate=May 8, 2010}}</ref> Both Watson and Glover were students at the school.<ref>{{cite web|author=The Committee Office, House of Commons |url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200203/cmselect/cmcumeds/458/458w125.htm |title=Appendix 124 Memorandum submitted by Margaret and James Watson |publisher=Publications.parliament.uk |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| April 23, 1991\n| [[Compton, California]], United States\n|\n| 1 dead\n|\n| A teenager aimed and fired a handgun at a security guard who had chased him and three friends off the grounds of Ralph J. Bunche Middle School. However, instead of hitting his intended target, the bullet struck 11-year-old bystander Alejandro Vargas, a student at the school, killing him.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://articles.latimes.com/1991-04-24/local/me-536_1_security-guard |title=Shot Fired at Guard Kills Boy at School |publisher=Articles.latimes.com |date=1991-09-19 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |first1=Ron |last1=Russell |first2=Michele |last2=Fuetsch}}</ref>\n|-\n| May 9, 1991\n| [[Reserve, Louisiana]], United States\n| Brenda Carter, 16\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 19-year-old senior Debbie Morantes is stabbed to death by 16-year-old sophomore Brenda Carter inside the cafeteria of East St. John High School. Brenda Carter was convicted of second-degree murder two years later.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=AD&p_theme=ad&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0EB4765F795DECFF&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM |title=LaPlace girl booked with murder of schoolmate |publisher=Nl.newsbank.com |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=AD&p_theme=ad&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0EB477531F5A8C2D&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM |title=Teen's sentencing set for next month |publisher=Nl.newsbank.com |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| June 19, 1991\n| [[Coffs Harbour]], Australia\n| ...,13\n| \n| \n| A student brought a rifle to [[Orara High School]] injuring 2 teachers and 1 student. The shooter was tackled to the ground by fellow students.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.apnewsarchive.com/1991/Student-Shoots-Three-Outside-His-School/id-9a37235e1f46bbf7d2e0acc5415db1b8|title=Student Shoots Three Outside His School|website=www.apnewsarchive.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| September 30, 1991\n| [[Indianapolis, Indiana]], United States\n| Edward C. Ector, 15\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 17-year-old Bertram Bowman is stabbed to death in the cafeteria of [[Arlington High School (Indianapolis)|Arlington High School]], reportedly in a dispute over a girl. Police arrested 15-year-old Edward C. Ector after the attack.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=aA0gAAAAIBAJ&sjid=o2UFAAAAIBAJ&pg=1533,76036&dq=school+stabbing&hl=en |title=Teen stabbed to death at school |publisher=News.google.ca |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=1sBJAAAAIBAJ&sjid=ohANAAAAIBAJ&pg=3661,77460&dq=school+stabbing&hl=en |title=Stabbing draws attention to violence in high schools |publisher=News.google.ca |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=1cBJAAAAIBAJ&sjid=ohANAAAAIBAJ&pg=4845,14264&dq=bertram+bowman&hl=en |title=School argument results in killing |publisher=News.google.com |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| October 9, 1991\n| [[New York City, New York]], United States\n|\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 17-year-old Tryon Whittaker was shot to death by another youth outside of James Monroe High School in [[The Bronx]]. The boys had reportedly got into an argument and Whittaker challenged the other youth to a fight. The youth then walked away but returned with a gun and shot Whittaker.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1991/10/09/nyregion/a-bronx-youth-is-shot-to-death-outside-a-school.html |title=A Bronx Youth Is Shot to Death Outside a School |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=1991-10-09 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |first=John T. |last=McQuiston}}</ref>\n|-\n| November 14, 1991\n| [[Houston, Texas]], United States\n| ..., 16\n|\n| 1 injured\n| 18-year-old Francisco Contreras was shot four times in his feet and leg outside the cafeteria of [[Milby High School]], in [[Houston]], [[Texas]], by a 16-year-old student, who was arrested afterward.<ref>\"[http://www.chron.com/CDA/archives/archive.mpl?id=1991_822573 Shooting at school fuels calls for more security].\" ''[[Houston Chronicle]]''. November 15, 1991.</ref>\n|-\t\n| November 25, 1991\n| [[New York City, New York]], United States\n| Jason Bentley, 14\n| 1 dead\n|\n| [[Thomas Jefferson High School (Brooklyn)|Thomas Jefferson High School]] A stray bullet kills a 16-year-old student during an argument between two other teens. Shooter Jason Bentley, 14, is sentenced in 1992 to three to nine years in prison.<ref name=\"PAC\"/>\n|-\t\n| February 26, 1992\n| [[New York City, New York]], United States\n| Kahlil Sumpter, 15\n| 2 dead\n|\n| [[Thomas Jefferson High School (Brooklyn)|Thomas Jefferson High School]] was the scene of its second shooting of the school year, when a 15-year-old shot and killed two other students. The shooter, Kahlil Sumpter, is sentenced in 1993 to between 6 2/3 and 20 years in prison and is released in 1998.<ref name=\"PAC\"/>\n|-\n| May 1, 1992\n| [[Olivehurst, California]], United States\n| Eric Houston, 20\n| 4 dead\n| 10 injured\n| [[Lindhurst High School shooting]]. Armed with a pistol, 20-year-old Eric Houston took hostages at his former high school, killing four people and wounding 10. His motive was his inability to find a good job because he had failed a grade at school. He was given the [[death penalty]] for the shooting.\n|-\n| May 14, 1992\n| [[Napa, California]], United States\n| John McMahan, 14\n|\n| 2 injured\n| Armed with a [[.357 Magnum|.357-caliber]] [[pistol]], 14-year-old student John McMahan opened fire in a science classroom, wounding two.<ref name=\"Understanding lethal school violence\">{{cite book|last = Moore|first = Mark H.|author2=Carol V. Petrie |author3=Anthony A. Braga |author4=Brenda L. McLaughlin |title = Deadly Lessons: Understanding Lethal School Violence|publisher= [[National Academies Press]]|year = 2003|location = Washington, D.C.|page = 294|url = http://www.nap.edu/openbook.php?isbn=0309084121}}</ref>\n|-\n| September 11, 1992\n| [[Amarillo, Texas]], United States\n| Randy Earl Matthews, 17; ..., 15\n|\n| 6 injured\n| Six students were shot at [[Palo Duro High School]], all survived the shooting. Police later arrested 17-year-old Randy Earl Matthews and an unidentified 15-year-old boy in connection with the shooting.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1992/09/12/us/student-wounds-6-at-high-school.html |title=Student Wounds 6 at High School |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=1992-09-12 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| September 21, 1992\n| [[New York City, New York]], United States\n| Michael Bubb, 15\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Damion Ennis, 15, is stabbed to death by a fellow student in a hallway of South Shore High School.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1992/09/22/nyregion/boy-15-is-fatally-stabbed-at-school-in-brooklyn.html |title=Boy, 15, Is Fatally Stabbed at School in Brooklyn |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=1992-09-22 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |first=Robert D. |last=McFadden}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 18, 1993\n| [[Grayson, Kentucky]], United States\n| Scott Pennington, 17\n| 2 dead\n|\n| Scott Pennington shot and killed teacher Deanna McDavid and custodian Marvin Hicks after entering McDavid's classroom at East Carter High School. Pennington was later found guilty of the murders and sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>[http://www2.indystar.com/library/factfiles/crime/school_violence/school_shootings.html School Shootings] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110717151825/http://www2.indystar.com/library/factfiles/crime/school_violence/school_shootings.html |date=2011-07-17 }}. .indystar.com. Retrieved on 2010-08-16.</ref>\n|-\n| February 1, 1993\n| [[Amityville, New York]], United States\n| Shem S. McCoy, 17\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| Shem S. McCoy, 17, shot two people, both cousins of his, at Amityville High School. One of those shot, Randel Artis, would die of his gunshot injuries. The three boys had apparently been engaged in a long running dispute.<ref>{{cit